# Documentation Governance Rule

- Before creating or substantially rewriting any file under `docs/`, read the closest matching template in `docs/templates/` first and follow its structure.
- New docs should include a `Template used` field in document control (or equivalent metadata) that references the template path.
- Keep `docs/tech-stack.md` concise; place deep policy detail in design/plan docs.
- If behavior, architecture, testing policy, or release gates change, update:
  - `docs/product-requirements-v1.md`
  - `docs/technical-design-v1.md`
  - `docs/design-wireframe-v1.md` (when UI flows or states change)
  - `docs/development-plan-v1.md` (editioned execution plan from `docs/templates/development-plan-template.md`; superseded editions stay linked under **Baseline / superseded plans**); optional **`docs/development-plan.md`** pointer document to the active edition only
  - `docs/tech-stack.md` summary references
- Maintain consistent naming for skills, packages, and workspace paths.
- Add a short revision-history note when materially changing policy.
- Prefer clear rationale and explicit assumptions over vague statements.
